CHALLENGE
Links in GPT can be formatted in different ways such as showing a clickable URL, a text URL, or a formatted link. If you have additional source citation requirements then it can get complicated to know that to say in your prompt to get the final version you need.

SOLUTION
The solution so far has been to experiment and take notes.

PROMPTS
* This will provide links where keywords are clickable formatted links:

  Add useful inline links.

* This will provide formatted links within () and use sources to support the text.

  Add links to supporting sources.

* These requests can be combined.

  Add both useful inline links and links to supporting sources.

* You can request specific reference cituation standards:

  Write supporting sources in MLA format.

  Write supporting sources in APA format.
